Prosper Loan Data Exploration¶

by Puneet Sharma¶

Investigation Overview¶

What factors affect a loan’s outcome status?
What affects the borrower’s APR or interest rate?
Are there differences between loans depending on how large the original loan amount was?

Dataset Overview¶

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others.

Note that the above cells have been set as "Skip"-type slides. That means that when the notebook is rendered as http slides, those cells won't show up.

Interest Rate vs Credit Score with Loan Status¶

Lender: Give loan to people with high Credit Score.
Borrower: Keep up your Credit Score to get good Interest Rate and higher loan amount.

plt.figure(figsize=[20, 10])

plt.ylim(350, 950);

Interest Rate vs Bank Card Utilization with Loan Status and Loan Amount¶

Lender: People getting good Interest Rate are likely end up having good status.
Borrower: High Bank Card Utilization will likely cause high Interest Rate and smaller Loan Amount.
